Description: Coyote Case is a revolutionary new smartphone case that protects you.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Coyote Case is a revolutionary new smartphone case that protects you. This sleek and durable smartphone case contains a powerful, personal panic siren coupled with an automated, Bluetooth-enabled safety app. When the button on the Coyote Case is activated, a 100+ decibel piercing siren deters a would-be attacker while alerting others in the immediate area of your need for help. At the same time, the Coyote Case app automatically sends an SMS text alert with your GPS location coordinates to your pre-selected emergency contacts. As time is of the essence, no further fumbling with your smartphone is required; it’s truly one-push personal protection. You can also set the case to, notify your contacts that you need help in silent mode or use it as a siren-only depending on your preferences. Coyote Case protects your personal safety and gives you greater peace of mind in almost any situation. For college students, young professionals, teens and their parents, Coyote Case is an added layer of security to protect loved ones from assault or undue harm. For joggers, adventure-lovers, travelers, those with chronic health conditions and the elderly, Coyote Case is a smart safety and independence ally. The idea for Coyote Case was inspired by a father concerned with the safety of his family and others. Founder Jonathan Page spent nearly a year working closely with skilled mechanical and electrical engineers, expert designers and developers, and valued consultants to deliver a revolutionary and reliable personal security system in the convenience of a smartphone case. His vision is to empower individuals to travel freely and with confidence having the powerful protection of the Coyote Case close at hand.

Full Description: Jobulous is an online job board and social network designed to help job seekers know more about would-be employers.  Jobulous seeks to create a vibrant online community for the free exchange of detailed job information.  For the first time, job candidates will have access to the critically important, mostly elusive information about what it is actually like to work at a company—based on anonymous first-hand reviews.  The site provides user-generated ratings based on both tangible and intangible metrics, including employee compensation, benefits, career advancement opportunities, corporate culture, work environment, and more.   Jobulous allows applicants to search detailed information about an industry, location, company, or even a job title based on the reviews of current and past employees. This anonymous community will give users the comfort to speak freely and openly about a company, a department, or a specific job.  Jobulous' mission is a simple one: to provide transparency to the work world. Currently there is none. Transparency in the work world will make the job search process far more efficient for  both employers and employees.

Description: Ribl is a location-based message board mobile app where users can share and discover the most relevant content about their current vicinity.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Ribl is a real-time, location-based message board mobile app where users can post and consume the most relevant content about their current vicinity so they’ll never miss out on what’s happening around them.  Riblers are connected by proximity so they can view posts from other riblers who are geographically close to them without having to “friend” or “follow” them. Riblers can post and consume text, articles, images, video, and audio about cool things happening around their current location.  Riblers can also “boost” the most interesting posts, which will increase the content’s geographical reach beyond the location where it was created. Additionally, a post’s geographical reach will decrease as time elapses. Thus, the content that shows up in a ribler’s feed is either hyper-local to her current location or very highly boosted, and recent. This proprietary algorithm will ensure that the user will only see the most recent, locally-relevant and highest-impact content.

Description: Upstream Technologies is a leading technology provider for the Separate Accounts Industry.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Upstream Technologies is a leading technology provider for the Separate Accounts Industry. The Upstream platform is highly scalable and seamlessly integrates into an organization’s existing separate accounts infrastructure. Their platform drives operational efficiencies by enabling a single portfolio manager to manage thousands of individual portfolios or a high net worth account manager to actively manage clients in an intuitive, consistent way. Through a user-friendly, web-based front end, Upstream’s platform helps managers embed their particular investment insights into all of their portfolios and automates many of the labor-intensive and error-prone tasks typically associated with managing separate accounts. Automated processes include raising or investing cash, harvesting gains and losses, enforcing compliance and managing dispersion. Uniquely, the platform also automates the handling of client restrictions, legacy holdings, and other exceptions. By continuously monitoring each portfolio based upon thresholds and predicted tracking error from specified benchmarks or model accounts, Upstream’s solution quickly identifies those particular accounts that require attention.
